  "prompt": "What kind of clothes should I wear for a home date?",
  "response": "For a home date, the key is to strike a balance between comfort and looking put-together. Here are some outfit ideas depending on the vibe of the date:\n\n### **Casual and Cozy Date**\n- **For Men**: A soft, well-fitted Henley or a casual button-up shirt paired with jeans or chinos. You can also wear a plain t-shirt with a relaxed cardigan or hoodie.\n- **For Women**: A cute sweater or a loose blouse with leggings or joggers. You could also opt for a maxi dress or a casual jumpsuit for a more polished look.\n\n### **Comfortable but Stylish**\n- **For Men**: A fitted t-shirt or polo shirt with slim-fit joggers or chinos. Add a casual jacket or flannel shirt for a laid-back vibe.\n- **For Women**: A cozy knit sweater with high-waisted jeans or a skirt. You could also wear a casual blouse with wide-leg pants.\n\n### **Romantic and Intimate**\n- **For Men**: A button-up shirt with dark jeans or tailored pants. Roll up the sleeves for a relaxed yet polished appearance.\n- **For Women**: A silky blouse with skinny jeans or a midi skirt. A slip dress or a figure-flattering jumpsuit can also work well.\n\n### **Extra Tips**\n- **Footwear**: Keep it simple with sneakers, loafers, or slip-ons for men, and ballet flats, ankle boots, or comfy sandals for women.\n- **Accessories**: Add a watch, minimalist jewelry, or a nice scarf to elevate the look without overdoing it.\n- **Fabric**: Opt for soft, breathable fabrics like cotton, cashmere, or linen for extra comfort.\n\nUltimately, the outfit should reflect your personality and make you feel confident and relaxed. And don\u2019t forget to add a spritz of your favorite fragrance! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
